Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal impairment (elevated creatinine), proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting possible acute or chronic kidney disease with impaired concentrating ability. Low HbA1c with glucosuria and ketonuria may indicate recent-onset or poorly controlled diabetes or another metabolic disturbance. Urine findings do not suggest infection. Further clinical correlation and nephrology/endocrinology evaluation are recommended.
